  "prompt": "What is the best time to visit Kanniyakumari?",
  "response": "The best time to visit Kanniyakumari is during the winter months, from October to March, when the weather is pleasant and comfortable. Here are some details:\n\n1. Winter (October to March):\n- Ideal temperature: 18\u00b0C to 30\u00b0C\n- Clear skies\n- Perfect for sightseeing\n- Comfortable for outdoor activities\n- Best time for photography and sunrise/sunset views\n\n2. Avoid summer (April to June):\n- Very hot and humid\n- Temperatures can reach up to 38\u00b0C\n- Not comfortable for tourism\n\n3. Monsoon (July to September):\n- Heavy rainfall\n- Some tourist activities might be limited\n- Beautiful greenery during this season\n- Less crowded\n\n4. Special considerations:\n- December and January are peak tourist seasons\n- Sunrise and sunset views are particularly spectacular during winter months\n- Comfortable for beach and outdoor activities\n\nThe winter months provide the most comfortable conditions for exploring Kanniyakumari's attractions like the Vivekananda Rock Memorial, Thiruvalluvar Statue, and experiencing the unique confluence of three water bodies.",
